Priority: optional
Maintainer: Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: raidutils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Adaptec I2O compliant RAID controller management utilities
 The raidutil programs manage I2O-compliant RAID controllers,
 including in particular some Adaptec RAID controllers.  One can
 create/delete a RAID array, add/remove a hot spare drive to/from a
 RAID array, activate/silence the alarm, and get information about the
 status of the RAID array and disks.
